# Klipper MCU firmware config — FLSUN Q5, MKS Robin Nano v1.2 (STM32F103VET6)
#
# This is a Kconfig fragment. CI copies it to klipper/.config and runs
# `make olddefconfig` to fill in defaults, then asserts the key symbols below
# are still set (so a silently-wrong build fails instead of reaching a printer).
#
# Connection: the Pi talks to the board over the board's USB port, which is an
# onboard CH340 USB-serial chip wired to the STM32's USART3. So:
#   - firmware comm interface = Serial on USART3 (PB10/PB11) @ 250000
#   - on the Pi the board appears as /dev/serial/by-id/usb-1a86_USB_Serial-if00-port0
# No GPIO/UART soldering required. Matches Klipper's official printer-flsun-q5-2020.cfg.
#
# Flashing: `make` produces out/klipper.bin; CI then runs
#   ./scripts/update_mks_robin.py out/klipper.bin out/Robin_nano.bin
# and publishes it under BOTH names (Robin_nano.bin and Robin_nano35.bin) because
# the v1.2 SD bootloader expects one or the other depending on batch. A wrong name
# is simply ignored by the bootloader — no risk.

CONFIG_LOW_LEVEL_OPTIONS=y
CONFIG_MACH_STM32=y
CONFIG_MACH_STM32F103=y
CONFIG_STM32_FLASH_START_7000=y
CONFIG_STM32_CLOCK_REF_8M=y
CONFIG_SERIAL=y
CONFIG_STM32_SERIAL_USART3=y
CONFIG_SERIAL_BAUD=250000
